                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width=3D"negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle U_{1}=3DR_{1}=
-{n_{1}(n_{1}+1) \over 2}\,\!}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/8e64acd817a990bb0a4cc397d779d111a744b869" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; margin-right: -0.387ex; width:23.332ex; height:5.676ex;" =
alt=3D"{\displaystyle U_{1}=3DR_{1}-{n_{1}(n_{1}+1) \over 2}\,\!}"></span><=
/dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<dl><dd><dl><dd>where <i>n</i><sub>1</sub> is the sample size for sample 1,=
 and <i>R</i><sub>1</sub> is the sum of the ranks in sample&nbsp;1.</dd></d=
l></dd></dl>
<dl><dd><dl><dd>Note that it doesn't matter which of the two samples is con=
sidered sample&nbsp;1. An equally valid formula for <i>U</i> is</dd></dl></=
dd></dl>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-in=
line"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"=
display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=
=3D"{\displaystyle U_{2}=3DR_{2}-{n_{2}(n_{2}+1) \over 2}\,\!}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
