<p>The formula for the standard deviation is more complicated in the presen=
ce of tied ranks. If there are ties in ranks, <i>=CF=83</i> should be adjus=
ted as follows:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \sigma _{\text{ties}}=3D{\sqrt {{n_{1}n_{2}(n_{1}+n_{2}+1) \over 12}-{n_{=
1}n_{2}\sum _{k=3D1}^{K}(t_{k}^{3}-t_{k}) \over 12n(n-1)}}},\,}">
  <semantics>
